        <h2 class="card-title">Public Provident Fund(PPF)</h2>
        <p class="card-text">A PPF or Public Provident Fund is a savings scheme offered by the Government of India. The interest on the account is paid by the government of India and set every quarter. The applicable PPF interest rate for 1st July to 30th September 2019 (Q2 FY 2019-20) has been fixed at 7.9%.The principal and interest in the PPF account are guaranteed by the Government. Contributions to the account up to Rs 1.5 lakh per annum are tax-free. Interest on the PPF account is also tax-free. Thus, PPF gives a 3-fold tax benefit.</p>
        <u>Investment Amount: </u>
        {{#ifCond salary 150000}}
        <b><p class="card-text amount">₹1,50,000</p></b><br>
        {{else}}
        <b><p class="card-text amount">₹{{salary}}</p></b><br>
        {{/ifCond}}
